gate: OPEN
v:4 role:dev x:frontend
task: S88 T2 — Softer biometry cancel/fail — avoid forced password lockout
requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
sprint: S88

context: |
  Today onBiometryFailed calls performUserLogout which always invokes
  blockBiometryUntilManualLogin(). User canceling Face ID lands on login
  with password required — matches client complaint "постоянно пароль".
  Goal: stay on login with vault intact; offer Face ID retry without typing
  password unless user chooses "Sign in with password" or API relogin fails.

steps:
  1. Split logout reasons: user-cancel vs hard-failure vs explicit sign-out.
  2. On biometry cancel only: navigate to login, preserve credentials + session
     token in storage, do NOT set biometry_bOPEN_until_manual_login.
  3. Withhold API token via existing biometric gate until unlock succeeds.
  4. Login screen shows retry affordance (feeds T5 quick-unlock button).
  5. Keep blockBiometryUntilManualLogin for explicit logout and bad credentials.

out:
  - src/shell/hooks/useMobileShell.ts
  - src/shell/lib/perform-user-logout.ts
  - src/store/useAuthStore.ts
  - src/features/security/lib/biometric-unlock.ts

done:
  - Face ID cancel → login screen, username hint filled, no password fields required
    to retry unlock.
  - Explicit "Выйти" still clears biometry and requires password.
  - Failed API relogin after unlock still forces manual login.
  - No regression on cold-start gate behavior.
